nt with different experimental observations that accompany the fast\npropagation of cracks, namely, fractoluminescence (i.e., the emission of\nvisible light during rupture) and a complex morphology of post-mortem fracture\nsurfaces, which could be due to the sublimation of bubbles.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 May 2019 09:54:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 6 Nov 2019 10:56:35 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 17 Apr 2020 15:44:34 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 18 Sep 2020 15:19:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-15"}
